Quick start instructions
========================

Install required software (Ubuntu):
    sudo apt-get install python-dev libpq-dev python-pip virtualenvwrapper sqlite3


Clone the repository:
    git clone https://github.com/cellcounter/cellcounter.git


Create a virtual environment:
    mkvirtualenv -r requirements.txt env1
    (MAC USERS: virtualenv env1; source env1/bin/activate;)


Delete all easy_install setuptools things from env1/bin/python2.7 etc


Get this: http://python-distribute.org/distribute_setup.py
	Run it (python distribute_setup.py)


Use pip to install django-seo


Edit cellcounter/localsettings.py to contain the following:
DATABASES = {'default': {
    'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.sqlite3',
    'NAME': '/full/path/to/cellcounter/db.sql'
    }
}

DEBUG = True

***NOTE: you need to enter your own path in 'NAME' field***


Build the database:
    python manage.py syncdb


Migrate to the latest schema:
    python manage.py migrate


Collect the static files:
    python manage.py collectstatic


Run the Django webserver:
    python manage.py runserver


Browse to 127.0.0.1:8000


Pat yourself on the back if this worked...

